              <decoDesc/>
              <additions>
                <list>
                  <item n="1" xml:id="addition1">
                     <p>Greek vowels being occasionally added by a later hand (<foreign xml:lang="syr">ܰ, ܶ, ܺ, ܳ, ܽ andܳ ,</foreign>  e.g. foll. <locus from="100a" to="100a">100 a</locus> and <locus from="101a" to="101a">101 a</locus>).</p>
                  </item>
                  <item n="2" xml:id="addition2">
                     <locus from="25b" to="26"/>
                     <p>The points rukkākh and kushshāi occur on foll. 25 b and 26.</p>
                  </item>
                   <item n="3" xml:id="addition3">
                      <locus from="129" to="129"/>
                      <p><quote xml:lang="syr"><sic>ܕܠܗ ܫܘܒܚܐ ܠܥܠܡ ܥܠܡܝܢ ܐܡܝܢ. ܐܠܗܐ ܢܚܣܐ ܠܟܠ ܕܫܬܘܬܦ ܐܡܝܢ</sic>.</quote></p>
                   </item>
                   <item n="4" xml:id="addition4">
                      <p>Some lessons have been noted on the margins by later hands.</p>
                   </item>
                   <item n="5" xml:id="addition5">
                      <locus from="1a" to="1a"/>
                      <p>On fol. 1 a the Lord's Prayer is written in an ancient Arabic hand, now much effaced.</p>
                      <p><quote xml:lang="ar"><!-- ADD MISSING ARABIC --></quote></p>
                   </item>
                   <item n="6" xml:id="addition6">
                      <locus from="11b" to="11b"/>
                      <p>One <persName ref="">Gabriel</persName> has recorded his name on fol. 11 b:</p>
                      <p><quote xml:lang="syr"><sic>ܨܠܠܘ ܥܠ ܓܒܪܐܝܠ ܡܛܠ ܡܪܢ ܘܟܠ ܚܕ ܐܝܟ ܨܠܘܬܗ ܢܬܦܪܥ ܡܝܢ ܡܪܝܐ</sic></quote></p>
                   </item>
                </list>
              </additions>
